For passports, copy the front page and any page with the employee’s details on including endorsements, eg a work visa or Certificate of Entitlement to Right of Abode in the UK.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>For biometric residence permits, copy both sides.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Keep copies for 2 years after the person stops working for you.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Make sure you follow the law when it comes to <a href=\"/data-protection-your-business\" title=\"Data protection rules\">data protection.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Birth, adoption, registration or naturalisation certificates</h2>\n\n<p>Birth, adoption, registration or naturalisation are only proof of eligibility to work in the UK if they were issued in the:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>UK</li>\n  <li>Channel Islands</li>\n  <li>Isle of Man</li>\n  <li>Republic of Ireland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>A certificate on its own is not proof of eligibility to work in the UK. Another document will be needed, eg passport.</p>\n\n<h3>Birth certificate</h3>\n\n<p>A birth certificate must show the name of the holder and at least one of their parents. The certificate must be an original (not a copy).</p>\n\n<h3>Adoption certificate</h3>\n\n<p>An adoption certificate must show the name of at least one of the adoptive parents.</p>\n\n<h3>Naturalisation certificate</h3>\n\n<p>A naturalisation certificate must describe the holder as a British citizen.</p>\n\n<h2>Certificate of entitlement to right of abode</h2>\n\n<p>A certificate of entitlement to right of abode is only valid if it&rsquo;s in a current, valid passport.</p>\n\n<p>For help, contact the <abbr title=\"UK Border Agency\">UKBA</abbr> Sponsorship and Employers&rsquo; Helpline.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Employer and education providers’ helpline</strong> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#115;&#112;&#111;&#110;&#115;&#111;&#114;&#115;&#104;&#105;&#112;&#080;&#066;&#083;&#101;&#110;&#113;&#117;&#105;&#114;&#105;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#117;&#107;&#0