ctivities</li>\n  <li>number of days and hours per day that the child will appear in the performances or activities (including rehearsals)</li>\n  <li>what the child will earn</li>\n  <li>arrangements that you will make for the child in relation to, eg schooling and chaperoning</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You will also need to provide:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a statement by the child&rsquo;s parents in support of the application (this may be part of the application form)</li>\n  <li>the child&rsquo;s birth certificate or other evidence of age</li>\n  <li>two identical prints of a photograph of the child taken during the previous six months</li>\n  <li>a copy of the contract, draft contract or other documents containing details of the agreement regulating the child&rsquo;s appearance in the performance or the activity for which the licence is required</li>\n  <li>a letter from the child&rsquo;s school authorising their absence</li>\n  <li>a declaration, where the child is under 14 years of age, that the part they are acting or dancing can only be taken by a child of approximately the same age</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>An application fee is generally not payable.</p>\n\n<p>You should apply at least 21 days before the performance or activity is due to start.</p>\n\n<p>The local authority may interview you, the child and the child&rsquo;s parents during the process of determining your application and may request that the child is medically examined to ensure they are fit to participate.</p>\n\n<p>If your application is granted, you will be issued a licence specifying the arrangements for the child to take part in the performance or activity.</p>\n\n<h2>Conditions</h2>\n\n<p>Licences will be subject to a number of conditions.</p>\n\n<p>For example:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the number of days the child can be expected to perform </li>\n  <li>getting a matron/chaperone and for the child&rsquo;s education during the term of the licence.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Premises where performances or rehearsals are to take place must be approved by the local authority to ensure they are suitable for children.</p>\n\n<p>You will also be required to keep detailed records relating to the performance or activity and produce these for inspection on request.</p>\n\n<h2>Fines and penalties</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>If you allow a child to take part in an unlicensed performance, or fail to comply with any conditions attached to your licence, you are committing an offence and may be fined up to £1,000, imprisoned for up to three months or both.</p>\n</div>\n"},"tags":[{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}}],"related":[{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/child-employment.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/child-employment","title":"Child employment","format":"guide","updated_at":"2012-10-30T15:13:33+00:00"},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/chaperone-service-child-actors.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/chaperone-service-child-actors","title":"Chaperone service for child actors","format":"local_transaction","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:24:19+00:00"}]},{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/child-work-permit-england-wales.json","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/child-work-permit-england-wales","title":"Child work permit (England and Wales)","format":"licence","updated_at":"2012-10-22T15:21:35+00:00","details":{"need_id":"1","business_proposition":true,"description":"To employ a child in the UK, you may need to get a work permit from your local authority","language":"en","alternative_title":"","will_continue_on":"","continuation_link":"","licence_identifier":"9098-5-1","licence_short_description":"Apply to your local authority for a child work permit","licence_overview":"<p>If you want to employ a child you may need to obtain a work permit for that child from the local authority where your business is based.</p>\n\n<p>A child includes any person who has not yet reached compulsory school leaving age.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s illegal to employ children under the age of 13 unless they are taking part in a paid performance (eg a play or film), sport or modelling and you have obtained a child performance licence from the relevant local authority.</p>\n\n<h2>Conditions</h2>\n<p>Children aged 13 may only be employed if your local authority allows it and only on an occasional basis:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>by their parents in light agricultural or horticultural work</li>\n  <li>in categories of light work set out in local byelaws</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>There are strict rules governing the hours that children can work and the types of work they can do.</p>\n\n<p>Check with your local authority to see what kinds of work children are permitted to do in your area and whether a work permit is required.</p>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n<p>If a permit is required, you will need to complete an application form from your local authority providing details about:  </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your business </li>\n  <li>the child</li>\n  <li>the job which the child is to be employed to do</li>\n  <li>the hours which they&rsquo;ll be expected to work</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll also need to provide:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a statement by the child&rsquo;s parents that the child is fit to work and they agree to the employment (t