inal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>) is now called the Disclosure and Barring Service (<abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr>) - <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> checks are now called <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> checks.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The person being given a <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> check - &lsquo;the applicant&rsquo; - can check on the progress of their application using the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://secure.crbonline.gov.uk/enquiry/enquirySearch.do\" title=\"tracking service\">tracking service.</a></p>\n\n<p>The applicant, employer and organisation that applied for the search will see the results of the check.</p>\n\n<h2>The <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> certificate</h2>\n\n<p>Once the check is completed, the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> will send a certificate listing the results to both the applicant and the authorised person requesting the check. </p>\n\n<h3>Security features</h3>\n\n<p>Certificates have security features to prove they&rsquo;re genuine:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>a &lsquo;crown seal&rsquo; watermark repeated down the right hand side, visible both on the surface and when holding it up to the light</li>\n  <li>a background design featuring the word &lsquo;Disclosure&rsquo;, which appears in a wave-like pattern across both sides of the certificate; the pattern&rsquo;s colour alternates between blue and green on the reverse of the certificate</li>\n  <li>ink and paper that change colour when wet</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Certificates printed by the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> have these security features, but ones sent by email don&rsquo;t.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The security features for a <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> certificate issued before 1 December 2012 are the same as for the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> certificate.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>Reusing a <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> check</h3>\n\n<p>A <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> certificate only contains information from a <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> check on a certain date and for a particular purpose. It can be accepted at a later date, but the employer will have to decide if it&rsquo;s recent enough or suitable for the current purpose.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s also up to the employer to check that the applicant&rsquo;s identity matches the details on the certificate.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p><abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>-branded certificates should be treated the same as <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr>-branded certificates.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h3>If the applicant loses the certificate</h3>\n\n<p>If the applicant loses the certificate, or it&rsquo;s destroyed, the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> can&rsquo;t provide a replacement.</p>\n\n<h3>If there&rsquo;s a mistake on the certificate</h3>\n\n<p>If the certificate contains incorrect personal details or criminal record information, the applicant should let the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> know as soon as possible using the disputes form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/dbs-checking-service-guidance/af14-af15?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'Disputes form' (PDF, 147KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download &lsquo;Disputes form&rsquo; (PDF, 147KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The applicant can also <a href=\"/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/contact-disclosure-and-barring-service\" title=\"contact the DBS\">contact the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr></a>.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/arranging-checks-as-an-employer","slug":"arranging-checks-as-an-employer","order":4,"title":"Arranging checks as an employer","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The Criminal Records Bureau (<abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>) is now called the Disclosure and Barring Service (<abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr>) - <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> checks are now called <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> checks.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Employers should only arrange a <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> check on a successful job applicant. They can withdraw a job offer if the results show anything that would make the applicant unsuitable.</p>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do fewer than 100 checks a year can use an <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/services/ub/\" title=\"umbrella body\">umbrella body.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Registering with the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do more than 100 checks a year can deal with their own applications if they <a href=\"/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/contact-disclosure-and-barring-service\" title=\"contact the DBS to register\">register with the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr></a>. This costs £300, plus £5 for each additional &lsquo;counter signatory&rsquo; (people within an organisation who are allowed to handle <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> applications).</p>\n\n<p>Registered organisations must follow the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/dbs-checking-service-guidance/cop\" title=\"DBS code of practice\"><abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> code of practice.</a></p>\n\n<h3>The e-Bulk service</h3>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do more than 1,500 checks a year can use the <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> e-Bulk service, which can help reduce costs and waiting times for <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> checks.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/dbs-checking-service-guidance/ebulk-overview?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'e-Bulk service guidance' (PDF, 107KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘e-Bulk service guidance’ (PDF, 107KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Checks on carers</h2>\n\n<p>Employers providing care services for adults - eg in a care home - can use a service called <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.isaadultfirst.co.uk/guidance.aspx/\" title=\"DBS Adult First\"><abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> Adult First.</a></p>\n\n<p>This will confirm, usually within 2 days, if the applicant:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>can start work, as long as they&rsquo;re supervised</li>\n  <li>should wait for the results of an enhanced check</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The service costs an extra £6.</p>\n\n<h2>Employers in Scotland or Northern Ireland</h2>\n\n<p>Employers in Scotland can get a criminal records check from <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.disclosurescotland.co.uk/apply/employers/\" title=\"Apply for a disclosure\">Disclosure Scotland,</a> while employers in Northern Ireland should go through <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dojni.gov.uk/accessni\" title=\"Apply for a disclosure\">Access NI.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Overseas applicants</h2>\n\n<p>If the applicant is from overseas, the employer can ask their <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/travel-and-living-abroad/foreign-embassies-in-uk/\" title=\"foreign embassy\">foreign embassy</a> if it can get a similar check done in their country.</p>\n\n<h2>Employing ex-offenders</h2>\n\n<p>If you carry out criminal records checks, you must have a policy on employing ex-offenders. You must show it to any applicant who asks for it.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/dbs-checking-service-guidance/sample-policy-recruitment?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'Sample policy on the recruitment of ex-offenders' (PDF, 101KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Sample policy on the recruitment of ex-offenders’ (PDF, 101KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/dbs-barred-lists","slug":"dbs-barred-lists","order":5,"title":"DBS barred lists","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The Criminal Records Bureau (<abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>) and the Independent Safeguarding Authority (<abbr title=\"Independent Safeguarding Authority\">ISA</abbr>) have merged and are now called the Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS). <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> checks are now called DBS checks.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Jobs that involve caring for, supervising or being in sole charge of children or adults require an enhanced DBS check (previously called an enhanced <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> check). </p>\n\n<p>This includes checking whether someone is included in the 2 DBS &lsquo;barred lists&rsquo; (previously called <abbr title=\"Independent Safeguarding Authority\">ISA</abbr> barred lists) of individuals who are unsuitable for working with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>children</li>\n  <li>adults</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>It&rsquo;s against the law for employers to employ someone or allow them to volunteer in this kind of work if they&rsquo;re on one of the barred lists.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Referring someone to the DBS</h2>\n\n<p>Employers must refer someone to the DBS if they:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>sacked them because they harmed a child or adult</li>\n  <li>sacked them because they might have harmed a child or adult otherwise</li>\n  <li>were planning to sack them for either of these reasons, but the person resigned first</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>They can do this by filling in the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/dbs/dbs-referrals-guidance/dbs-referral-form?version=1\" title=\"ISA referral form\">DBS referral form.</a> The address is on the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>An employer is breaking the law if they don&rsquo;t refer someone to the DBS for any of these reasons.</p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/contact-disclosure-and-barring-service","slug":"contact-disclosure-and-barring-service","order":6,"title":"Contact the Disclosure and Barring Service","body":"\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>The Criminal Records Bureau (<abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>) is now called the Disclosure and Barring Service (<abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr>) - <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> checks are now called <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> checks.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Disclosure and Barring Service</strong><br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#099;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#111;&#109;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#101;&#114;&#118;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#100;&#098;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#099;&#117;&#115;&#116;&#111;&#109;&#101;&#114;&#115;&#101;&#114;&#118;&#105;&#099;&#101;&#115;&#064;&#100;&#098;&#115;&#046;&#103;&#115;&#105;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Telephone:</strong> 0870 909 0811<br />\n<strong>Minicom:</strong> 0870 909 0344</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The <abbr title=\"Disclosure and Barring Service\">DBS</abbr> has a confidential checking process for transgender applicants who don&rsquo;t want to reveal details of their previous identity to a potential employer.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contac