ustments from the Disability Employment Adviser (<abbr title=\"Disability Employment Adviser\">DEA</abbr>) at <a href=\"/contact-jobcentre-plus\" title=\"Contact Jobcentre Plus\">your local Jobcentre Plus office</a>.</p>\n\n<p>In Northern Ireland, you can get advice from the <a href=\"http://www.delni.gov.uk/index/finding-employment-finding-staff/fs-help-to-find-staff/fefs-recruit-and-retain-people-with-disabilities.htm http://www.delni.gov.uk/index/finding-employment-finding-staff/fs-help-to-find-staff/fefs-recruit-and-retain-people-with-disabilities.htm\" title=\"Contact the Disability Employment Service\" rel=\"external\">Disability Employment Service.</a>  </p>\n\n<p>There&rsquo;s more detail about employers&rsquo; obligations and how to meet them on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.equalityhumanrights.com/advice-and-guidance/guidance-for-employers/the-duty-to-make-reasonable-adjustments-for-disabled-people/\" title=\"the duty to make reasonable adjustments for disabled people\">Equality and Human Rights Commission website.</a></p>\n\n<p>You might also be able to get <a href=\"/access-to-work\" title=\"Access to Work: financial support for disabled workers\">financial support for making reasonable adjustments</a>.</p>\n\n","alternative_title":""},"tags":[{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.js