ill be based in the UK</li>\n  <li>minister of religion - for people coming to work for a recognised religious organisation (for up to 3 years)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Scotland</h3>\n\n<p>In Scotland, a skilled job offer has to be Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework (<abbr title=\"Scottish Credit and Qualifications Framework\">SCQF</abbr>) level 9 or above for both general work and intra-company transfers.</p>\n\n<h2>Tier 5 - temporary workers</h2>\n\n<p>Tier 5 sponsorship can be:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>creative and sporting - to work as a sportsperson (up to 12 months), entertainer or artist (up to 24 months)</li>\n  <li>charity worker - includes both paid and voluntary workers (up to 12 months)</li>\n  <li>religious worker - for those doing preaching, pastoral and non-pastoral work (24 months)</li>\n  <li>government authorised exchange - for those coming to the UK through an approved scheme (24 months)</li>\n  <li>international agreement - for those coming to the UK for a job that is covered under international law, eg. employees of overseas governments</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/uk-visa-sponsorship-employers/apply-for-a-sponsor-licence","slug":"apply-for-a-sponsor-licence","order":2,"title":"Apply for a sponsorship licence","body":"<p>When you apply for a sponsorship licence, you apply for an annual amount of <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/business-sponsors/points/sponsoringmigrants/applyforlicence/annual-allocation/\" title=\"Unrestricted certificates of sponsorship\">unrestricted certificates of sponsorship.</a>  You can also apply for <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/business-sponsors/points/sponsoringmigrants/employingmigrants/apply-for-restricted-cos/\" title=\"restricted certificates of sponsorship\">restricted certificates of sponsorship</a> during the year through the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/business-sponsors/points/sponsoringmigrants/sms/whatissms/\" title=\"Sponsorship Management System\">Sponsorship Management System.</a></p>\n\n<p>You can get a licence if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you aren’t in breach of immigration control</li>\n  <li>you can meet your sponsorship duties</li>\n  <li>you are an organisation or recognised religion operating legally in the UK </li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You may have to provide documents to prove your organisation is genuine and operating legally in the UK. &lsquo;Appendix A&rsquo; has more information about which documents are suitable.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/sitecontent/documents/employersandsponsors/pbsguidance/guidancefrom31mar09/appendix-a.pdf?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'Appendix A - list of documents' (PDF, 303KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Appendix A - list of documents’ (PDF, 303KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You must <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.points.homeoffice.gov.uk/gui-sponsor-jsf/SponsorHome.faces\" title=\"UK Border Agency\">apply online</a> for a sponsorship licence.</p>\n\n<h2>Where to send your documents and fees</h2>\n\n<p>You must send all supporting documents and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.ukba.homeoffice.gov.uk/business-sponsors/points/sponsoringmigrants/costs/costofalicence\" title=\"Application fees\">fees</a> to the UK Border Agency (<abbr title=\"UK Border Agency\">UKBA</abbr>).</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nSponsor casework operations  \n<br />Sponsor applications team  \n<br />UK Border Agency  \n<br />PO Box 3468  \n<br />Sheffield  \n<br />S3 8WA  \n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>All supporting documents must be original or certified copies, eg signed by a solicitor or notary. Any documents not given in English or Welsh need to be translated with the translator’s details included. Your application will be rejected if all the documents aren’t sent in.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re successful the <abbr title=\"UK Border Agency\">UKBA</abbr> w